yarn add @react-navigation/stack
```
4. Once the installation is complete, you can import `createStackNavigator` from `@react-navigation/stack` in your React Native app and use it to create a stack navigator.

Here is an example of how to create a basic stack navigator using `createStackNavigator`:
```javascript
import { createStackNavigator } from '@react-navigation/stack';
import { NavigationContainer } from '@react-navigation/native';
import React from 'react';

const Stack = createStackNavigator();

function App() {
  return (
    <NavigationContainer>
      <Stack.Navigator>
        <Stack.Screen name="Home" component={HomeScreen} />
        <Stack.Screen name="Details" component={DetailsScreen} />
      </Stack.Navigator>
    </NavigationContainer>
  );
}

function HomeScreen() {
  return (
    // Your home screen component
  );
}

function DetailsScreen() {
  return (
    // Your details screen component
  );
}

export default App;
```
In this example, we created a stack navigator with two screens: `Home` and `Details`. You can replace the `HomeScreen` and `DetailsScreen` components with your own screen components.

